    "media:imagetext": "UNITED AIRLINES\nBoeing 737-322\nUnited accepted its first Boeing twin-jet in 1967, and has\noperated one of the world's largest 737 fleets ever since. In\n1986, the carrier added new advanced model 737-300s,\nwhich incorporate increased capacity, range and fuel effi-\nciency. The first to be delivered is shown on takeoff from\nRunway 22-Left at Chicago's O'Hare International Airport.\nPOST\nCARD\nRATE\nLitho in U.S.A.\nFLF-031\n37028470\nPOST CARD\nPhoto by David Campbell (December 21, 1986)\nN301UA — C/N 23642\nFlite-Line Fotocards\nPost Office Box 188\nBethel, CT 06801, U.S.A.\n2015:\n166.1663",
